text: Jonas Gahr Støre (born 25 August 1960) is a Norwegian politician. In 2021, Støre became the 36th Prime Minister of Norway. He is the leader of the Labour Party since 2014. He was Minister of Foreign Affairs from 2005 to 2012 and as Minister of Health and Care Services from 2012 to 2013. He has been a member of the Storting since 2009.Støre, Jonas Gahr ( 1960- ) Stortinget.no. Retrieved 7 November 2013. In September 2021, the Labour party won the most seats in the Storting making Støre the favorite to be the next Prime Minister of Norway. ==Related pages== *Cabinet of prime minister Støre ==References== Category:1960 births Category:Living people Category:Prime ministers of Norway Category:Current national leaders Category:Politicians from Oslo Category:Politicians from norway
